@startuml
title Parallel Roadmap Batch Automation - User Gates And Codex Automation

|User|
start
:Ask for next parallel batch
or discuss a new design;

|Codex Coordinator|
:Run workflow kickoff
parallel-roadmap-batch;
:Inspect git state,
roadmap docs,
owning roadmaps,
and code truth;

if (New or changed design?) then (yes)
  :Run architecture governance intake;
  :Fit design into lifecycle docs,
  decision register, triage,
  and dependency roadmap as needed;
else (no)
  :Use current register,
  triage, and checklist;
endif

:Select candidate rows by
gate, dependency level,
lane, and score;
:Reject blocked B5 work,
unaccepted ADR/design work,
and overlapping write scopes;
:Produce batch proposal with
worker prompts, write scopes,
validations, stop conditions,
and closeout docs;

|User|
:Review batch proposal;
if (Approve batch?) then (yes)
  |Codex Coordinator|
  :Create or name integration branch;
  :Prefer isolated worktrees
  or worker branches;

  |Codex Workers / Subagents|
  fork
    :Worker A inspects,
    implements, validates,
    reports files/functions;
  fork again
    :Worker B inspects,
    implements, validates,
    reports files/functions;
  fork again
    :Worker C inspects,
    implements, validates,
    reports files/functions;
  end fork

  |Codex Coordinator|
  :Review worker outputs
  and combined diff;
  if (Conflict, owner leak, or scope expansion?) then (yes)
    :Repair safely or reject
    the offending slice;
  else (no)
    :Accept bounded worker slices;
  endif

  :Update coordinator-level docs:
  checklist, decision register,
  triage, diagram, owning roadmaps;

  |Validation|
  :Run focused tests;
  :Run docs validation;
  :Run broader gates when
  cross-domain contracts changed;

  |Codex Coordinator|
  :Summarize completed slices,
  validation, blockers,
  and next recommended batch;

  |User|
  :Review final result
  and decide merge/commit;
  stop
else (no)
  |User|
  :Discuss changes,
  remove rows, or adjust scope;
  |Codex Coordinator|
  :Revise proposal only;
  stop
endif

legend right
  <b>User responsibilities</b>
  - Provide goal or new design topic
  - Approve or reject the proposed batch
  - Review final summary / decide merge

  <b>Codex automation</b>
  - Inspect roadmap docs and code truth
  - Propose parallelizable work
  - Generate worker prompts and scopes
  - Spawn workers when approved
  - Integrate, validate, and update docs
endlegend

@enduml
